cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY. 

This paper deals with software engineering and machine learning techniques to predict the acceptance of pull requests in software development. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of predictors and features to predict the acceptance of pull requests could also be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
